description: Full planning application for the redevelopment of part of the existing Sainsbury's car-park, comprising a part 4-, 5- and 7-storey building with 90 customer-parking spaces and 60 residential-parking spaces (including 10 parking spaces for affordable-housing use beneath the building and 6 disabled-parking spaces in the Sainsbury's customer car-park) and 103 cycle-parking spaces (35 in the residential car-park and 68 along the front of the building) at lower ground level, 23 x 1-bedroom flats, 76 x 2-bedroom flats, 9 x 3-bedroom flats (with 50% affordable housing), associated amenity space and landscaping, and subject to a Deed of Agreement dated 09/06/2005 under Section 106 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended)
